Capstone 2: Historical EV Sales Analysis

Hypothesis: The analysis aims to explore the potential relationship between the sales of Electric Vehicles (EV) and the availability of charging infrastructure, using historical data. It seeks to conduct a thorough examination of the sales trends of both Battery Electric Vehicles (BEV) and Plug-In Hybrid Vehicles (PHEV) types and their historical correlation with the development and distribution of slow and fast public charging points.

Analysis:

EV Sales & Charging Points over time:

In[30]:
# Line Graph of EV sales & EV charging points over time
plot = sns.relplot(x="year", y="value",
                   hue="parameter",  
                   data=df_ctry_prm_ctg,
                   kind="line",
                   errorbar=None)

# Set x-axis and y-axis labels
plot.set_axis_labels('Year', 'Quantity')

# Set the title of the plot
plot.fig.suptitle('EV Sales & EV Charging Points Over Time', y=1.03)  # Adjust y for spacing

# Show plot
plt.show()

Insights:

  • Sales grew substantially between 2020 and 2022.
  • Public charging point availability started to grow in 2018.
  • As sales have been increasing also has the public charging point infrastructure.

Growth Rate of EV sales & Charging Points over Time

In[31]:
# Filter the DataFrame for EV sales and EV charging points
ev_sales_charging_df = df_ctry_prm_ctg[df_ctry_prm_ctg['parameter'].isin(['EV sales', 'EV charging points'])]

# Group by year and parameter, then sum the values
sum_by_year_parameter = ev_sales_charging_df.groupby(['year', 'parameter'])['value'].sum().reset_index(name='total_count')

# Calculate the year-over-year growth rate
sum_by_year_parameter['growth_rate'] = sum_by_year_parameter.groupby('parameter')['total_count'].pct_change() * 100

# Display the DataFrame with growth rates
print(sum_by_year_parameter)

# Plotting the growth rate line graph
sns.lineplot(data=sum_by_year_parameter, x='year', y='growth_rate', hue='parameter', marker='o')
plt.title('Year-over-Year Growth Rate of EV Sales and EV Charging Points')
plt.xlabel('Year')
plt.ylabel('Growth Rate (%)')
plt.legend(title='Parameter')
plt.show()

# Filter the DataFrame for EV sales and EV charging points
ev_sales_charging_df = df_ctry_prm_ctg[df_ctry_prm_ctg['parameter'].isin(['EV sales', 'EV charging points'])]

# Group by region, year, and parameter, then sum the values
sum_by_region_year_parameter = ev_sales_charging_df.groupby(['country', 'year', 'parameter'])['value'].sum().reset_index(name='total_count')

# Calculate the year-over-year growth rate for each country
sum_by_region_year_parameter['growth_rate'] = sum_by_region_year_parameter.groupby(['country', 'parameter'])['total_count'].pct_change() * 100

# Display the DataFrame with growth rates
print(sum_by_region_year_parameter)

# Plotting the growth rate line graph at the country level
plt.figure(figsize=(15, 10))
g = sns.relplot(x="year", y="growth_rate",
                hue="parameter",  
                col="country",  # Specify country column to create separate graphs
                col_wrap=3,  # Number of columns per row
                data=sum_by_region_year_parameter,
                kind="line",
                marker='o',
                facet_kws={'sharey': False})  # Allow different y-axis scales for each subplot

# Adjust the titles and labels for readability
g.set_titles("{col_name}")
g.set_axis_labels("Year", "Growth Rate (%)")
g.add_legend(title="Parameter")
plt.suptitle('Year-over-Year Growth Rate of EV Sales and EV Charging Points by Country', y=1.02)

BEV vs PHEV Sales Over Time

In[34]:
# Filter the DataFrame for EV and PHEV sales
ev_phev_sales_df = df_ctry_prm_ctg[df_ctry_prm_ctg['parameter'] == 'EV sales']

# Group by year and powertrain, then sum the values
sum_by_year_powertrain = ev_phev_sales_df.groupby(['year', 'powertrain'])['value'].sum().reset_index(name='total_count')

# Custom formatter function to avoid scientific notation and add commas
def comma_formatter(x, pos):
    return '{:,.0f}'.format(x)

# Plotting the line graph
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
sns.lineplot(data=sum_by_year_powertrain, x='year', y='total_count', hue='powertrain')
plt.title('BEV vs PHEV Sales per Year')
plt.xlabel('Year')
plt.ylabel('Total Sales')
plt.legend(title='Sales Type')

# Apply comma formatter to y-axis
plt.gca().yaxis.set_major_formatter(FuncFormatter(comma_formatter))

# Show plot
plt.show()

Insights:

  • BEV sales has been greater than PHEV sales since 2013
  • Both BEV and PHEV sales significantly increased from 2020 - 2022

In[55]:
# Filter the DataFrame for BEV and PHEV separately
bev_df = sum_by_country_powertrain_sorted[sum_by_country_powertrain_sorted['powertrain'] == 'BEV']
phev_df = sum_by_country_powertrain_sorted[sum_by_country_powertrain_sorted['powertrain'] == 'PHEV']

# Create new columns for BEV Total and PHEV Total
sum_by_country_powertrain_sorted['BEV Total'] = bev_df.groupby('country')['total_count'].transform('sum')
sum_by_country_powertrain_sorted['PHEV Total'] = phev_df.groupby('country')['total_count'].transform('sum')

# Define colors for BEV and PHEV bars
bev_color = 'skyblue'
phev_color = 'salmon'

# Unique countries
countries = sum_by_country_powertrain_sorted['country'].unique()

# Calculate BEV and PHEV totals per country
bev_totals = [sum_by_country_powertrain_sorted[sum_by_country_powertrain_sorted['country'] == country]['BEV Total'].sum() for country in countries]
phev_totals = [sum_by_country_powertrain_sorted[sum_by_country_powertrain_sorted['country'] == country]['PHEV Total'].sum() for country in countries]

# X-axis positions
x = np.arange(len(countries))

# Bar width
bar_width = 0.35

# Custom formatter function to add commas
def comma_formatter(x, pos):
    return '{:,.0f}'.format(x)

# Plotting BEV and PHEV totals by country
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 6))

# BEV bars
bar1 = ax.bar(x - bar_width / 2, bev_totals, bar_width, label='BEV Total', color=bev_color)

# PHEV bars
bar2 = ax.bar(x + bar_width / 2, phev_totals, bar_width, label='PHEV Total', color=phev_color)

# Set x-axis labels
ax.set_xlabel('Country')
ax.set_ylabel('Total Count')
ax.set_title('Total Count of BEV and PHEV by Country')
ax.set_xticks(x)
ax.set_xticklabels(countries, rotation=45, ha='right')

# Apply comma formatter to y-axis
ax.yaxis.set_major_formatter(FuncFormatter(comma_formatter))

# Add legend
ax.legend()

# Adjust layout
fig.tight_layout()

# Show plot
plt.show()

Insights:

  • China has the highest sales in both BEV and PHEV, followed by USA then Germany
  • Sweden, Belgium, Spain, Finland are the only countries with higher PHEV sales than BEV
